cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of foreground pixel labelling in video surveillance using deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new model architecture that incorporates ideas from inception modules and residual networking, which are commonly used in deep learning for image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with video surveillance, which has security implications, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
